17/09/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Bucharest Mayor Traian Basescu, who leads the opposition Democratic Party, is signalling that he could be tapped for the post of prime minister if the alliance with the National Liberal Party wins the elections. Local media reported Thursday (16 September) that Basescu, who had rejected the idea during the past several months, is no longer ruling it out. The general elections are scheduled for 28 November. 
In other news, Romania filed a case against Ukraine with the International Court of Justice on Thursday. At issue is a dispute over the two countries' border across the northern section of the Black Sea. (Monitorul, Rompres, Nine o'clock - 17/09/04) 
